The government approved, on Wednesday, "The National Strategy on Immigration for 2015-2018" and "The Action Plan for the Year in progress", documents considered to be "a further step that Romania is going through in its efforts to modernise the immigration management process in the national territory", according to a press release.
The source indicated that the strategy aims to effectively manage the phenomenon of immigration, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and action directions that reflect policies set at European level adapted to national realities.
